  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rational Functional Tester Extension for Terminal-based Applications (FTE) is used to automate the testing of MVS, VM,&#xD;
    OS/400 and Unix host applications.&amp;nbsp; This tool mentor assumes you have installed the Rational Functional Tester&#xD;
    Extension and have some familiarity with Rational Functional Tester (RFT).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You may want to create a host test script that does not login to the host; for example, for&amp;nbsp;security&#xD;
    reasons.&amp;nbsp;This tool mentor describes how to create a script from a non-login screen; that is, a script that is&#xD;
    intended to run after the connection to the host has been established.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Tool Steps&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Begin the script creation by&amp;nbsp;launching&amp;nbsp;FTE from a Rational Functional Tester project outside of recording&#xD;
        a test script.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Enter&amp;nbsp;your host connection parameters and connect to the host system.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Once the connection is successful, login to&amp;nbsp;your host system.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Navigate to&amp;nbsp;the first screen&amp;nbsp;you want to test.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        With the FTE window still open, start recording a script within Rational Functional Tester by pressing the &quot;Record&#xD;
        a Functional Test Script&quot; button.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Next, place the&amp;nbsp;focus on the FTE&amp;nbsp;window and perform the host actions you want to test.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Logoff from the host and close the FTE window.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        You may now stop recording of the script.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To run the script, launch FTE again.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Start a connection to the same host, log into your host system, and navigate to the screen where the script starts.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        You may now&amp;nbsp;run the script.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol></mainDescription>
